<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1792,2070]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,351,1792,1818]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">Typification note:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authority="Kurz" authorityName="Kurz" authorityYear="1871" box="[379,739,1792,1819]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lythraceae" genus="Ammannia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simpliciuscula">
<emphasis box="[379,673,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">Ammannia simpliciuscula</emphasis>
Kurz
</taxonomicName>
was described based on his own collection from 
<collectingCountry box="[1320,1447,1792,1818]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">Chittagong</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[136,270,1828,1854]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
, which was later circumscribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Koehne, B. A." box="[674,845,1828,1854]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" pagination="159 - 175" refId="ref3067" refString="Koehne, B. A. (1880) Lythraceae, In: Engler, A. (Ed.) Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte and Pflanzengeographie 1 (2): 159 - 175. [Leipzig]" type="journal article" year="1880">Koehne (1880)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurz" authorityYear="1871" box="[885,1080,1828,1854]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lythraceae" genus="Ammannia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simpliciuscula">
<emphasis box="[885,1080,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">R. simpliciuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, C. D. K." box="[1096,1239,1828,1854]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" pagination="1 - 156" refId="ref2781" refString="Cook, C. D. K. (1979) A revision of the genus Rotala (Lythraceae). Boissiera 29: 1 - 156. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1219622" type="journal article" year="1979">Cook (1979)</bibRefCitation>
designated Kurz’s specimen in 
<collectionCode box="[276,331,1864,1890]" country="India" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" name="Botanical Survey of India" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" type="Herbarium">CAL</collectionCode>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[406,509,1864,1890]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">lectotype</typeStatus>
(without seeing the material). We examined the possible specimen 
<collectionCode box="[1255,1311,1864,1890]" country="India" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" name="Botanical Survey of India" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" type="Herbarium">CAL</collectionCode>
0000010199 at 
<collectionCode box="[164,219,1900,1926]" country="India" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" name="Botanical Survey of India" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" type="Herbarium">CAL</collectionCode>
and found that of the two pockets on the top left corner, one is empty whereas the other contains fragmented leaves and remnant of a broken stem, which is demonstrably ambiguous and cannot be critically identified for the purpose of precise application of the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurz" authorityYear="1871" box="[600,791,1972,1998]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lythraceae" genus="Ammannia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simpliciuscula">
<emphasis box="[600,791,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">R. simpliciuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, another complete collection of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurz" authorityYear="1871" box="[1261,1452,1972,1998]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lythraceae" genus="Ammannia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simpliciuscula">
<emphasis box="[1261,1452,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">R. simpliciuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<collectionCode box="[171,185,2009,2035]" country="South Africa" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14647" name="University of the Witwatersrand" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" type="Herbarium">J</collectionCode>
. D. Hooker and Thomson available at 
<collectionCode box="[614,639,2009,2035]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15637" name="Botanische Staatssammlung München" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" type="Herbarium">M</collectionCode>
(
<collectionCode box="[653,678,2008,2035]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15637" name="Botanische Staatssammlung München" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" type="Herbarium">M</collectionCode>
0146229) is designated as epitype in accordance with Art. 9.9 of 
<collectionCode box="[1403,1451,2008,2034]" country="Colombia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/xsgz-nxkh" name="Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Museo de Historia Natural" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">ICN</collectionCode>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; Mcneill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[143,364,2044,2070]" pageId="4" pageNumber="171" pagination="159" refId="ref3610" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., Mcneill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="journal article" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[240,296,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="171">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
